      "content_blocks": [
        {
          "title": "The interface interrupt the gameplay",
          "block_paragraphs": [
            {"paragraph": "The stamina bar, due to its positioning, is uncomfortable to look at because it is too far from the center of the screen, where the character and enemies are located."},
            {"paragraph": "This becomes a problem because it requires the player to constantly take their eyes off the combat, resulting not in dynamic gameplay, but rather in an annoyance."}
          ],
          "block_multimedia": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "media": "/images/witcher/problem_v1.jpg",
              "note": ""
            },
            {
              "type": "image",
              "media": "/images/witcher/problem_v2.jpg",
              "note": ""
            },
            {
              "type": "image",
              "media": "/images/witcher/problem_v3.jpg",
              "note": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "title": "Industry references",
          "block_paragraphs": [
            {"paragraph": "Looking at the industry of Action RPG and exploring games we found some solutions to those problematics that would fit perfect into The Witcher 3."},
            {"paragraph": "In one hand we have games like Skyrim or Elden Ring, using a compass for navigating the world, a function even requested by the fans."},
            {"paragraph": "And for managing the stamina one of the best examples is Zelda with the Stamina Wheel and others games with resources management inside the sight."}
          ],
          "block_multimedia": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "media": "/images/witcher/referencia_1.jpg",
              "note": ""
            },
            {
              "type": "image",
              "media": "/images/witcher/referencia_2.jpg",
              "note": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "title": "Using what we know to solve the issue",
          "block_paragraphs": [
            {"paragraph": "The solution provided consisted in turning the stamina bar into a dynamic wheel that follows Geraldt body during combat."},
            {"paragraph": "For the navigation, the map was hidden and a compass was implemented and adapted."}
          ],
